law.text:
On request of a fire investigator, an insurer investigating a fire loss of real or personal property shall cooperate with and release to the fire investigator any information it has about the fire loss, including:
each insurance policy and application for the policy relevant to the fire loss;
policy premium payment records;
previous claims made by the insured for fire loss; and
material that relates to the investigation of the fire loss, proof of loss, and any other relevant evidence.
